  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I earn money with my studies?",
  "response": "Earning money while studying can be a great way to support yourself and gain valuable experience. Here are some ideas to consider:\n\n1. **Part-Time Jobs**: Look for jobs that allow you to work part-time, such as retail positions, hospitality jobs, or administrative work.\n\n2. **Tutoring**: If you excel in a particular subject, consider offering tutoring services to fellow students or younger learners.\n\n3. **Freelancing**: Utilize skills you have, such as writing, graphic design, programming, or social media management, by offering freelance services online.\n\n4. **Internships**: Seek paid internships related to your field of study. These positions can offer practical experience and networking opportunities.\n\n5. **Campus Jobs**: Many universities offer jobs for students, such as library assistants, lab technicians, or office work, which can be convenient and flexible.\n\n6. **Online Surveys and Market Research**: Participate in online surveys or market research studies that pay you for your opinions.\n\n7. **Sell Products or Crafts**: If you're crafty, sell handmade products on platforms like Etsy. Or consider dropshipping or reselling items online.\n\n8. **Blogging or Vlogging**: Share your studies and experiences on platforms like YouTube or a personal blog, and monetize through ads, sponsored content, or affiliate marketing.\n\n9. **Pet Sitting or House Sitting**: Offer pet sitting or house sitting services, which can be a flexible way to make money.\n\n10. **Social Media Management**: If you're savvy with social media, offer to manage accounts for local businesses or individuals.\n\n11. **Rent Out Your Space**: If you have a spare room or couch, consider renting it out on platforms like Airbnb.\n\n12. **Research Assistant**: If you're in college, ask professors if they need research assistants. These positions may be paid and provide valuable experience.\n\n13. **Delivery Services**: Work for food or parcel delivery services, which often have flexible schedules.\n\n14. **Gigs and Task-Based Work**: Use apps or platforms that connect you with short-term gigs, such as TaskRabbit or Fiverr.\n\n15. **Online Teaching**: Platforms like VIPKid allow you to teach English online to students around the world.\n\nBe sure to balance work with your studies to maintain a healthy academic performance. Choose options that allow for flexible hours or that align with your field of study to make the most of your time and efforts.",
